==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neo-Greek
<hw>Ne`o-Greek"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A member of a body of French
painters (F. <ets>les n⟦eacute⟧o-Grecs</ets>) of the middle 19th
century. The term is rather one applied by outsiders to certain artists
of grave and refined style, such as <persfn>Hamon</persfn> and
<persfn>Aubert</persfn>, than a name adopted by the artists
themselves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neo-Hebraic</ent>⟦br⟧
